sly:<br><br> <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1498084570i/23090207.jpg" width="460" height="460" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg" loading="lazy"><br><br>Therefore, I decided that the part where Lia lies to Pauline about something pretty significant was a good place to call it. <br><br>I'm not down with lying to people "for their own good," and I didn't feel like dealing with the contrived and predictable drama this lie would assuredly cause. <br><br>I was also bored by the made up songs and scriptures at the start of every chapter. And when those started to become longer than one page...Pfffft. Over and out homies. <br><br><a href="https://www.facebook.com/SteamyReadsBlog/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">
